      - Choice-value validation: <type>Complaint</type>,
        <status>Open</status>, <priority>High</priority> - capital C in
        Complaint, capital O in Open, capital H in High.
      - sys_id determinism check: <sys_id> equals MD5(subject) exactly
        (verified at file generation time:
        echo -n "Demo case 07: Open (Complaint)" | md5sum
        => d2a92d7d0645409519a05256350fc65e).
      - Cross-reference resolution check: the <assigned_group> text
        value matches sys_user_group_x_[scope]_demo_team.xml's <name>
        field; the <sys_scope> text value matches x_[scope].xml's
        <source> field; the <sys_package> source attribute matches
        x_[scope].xml's <source> field.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved verbatim in the
        sys_class_name, sys_update_name, all reference values, and the
        file path.

    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. Demo case 07 is the canonical Open Complaint case, AND is
         THE FIRST COMPLAINT CASE IN THE FIXTURE. The case_07 -> case_08
         hinge is the boundary between General Inquiry cases (01-06)
         and Complaint cases (07-10).
      2. The Complaint flow vs. General Inquiry flow: per AAP Section
         0.5.5, both flows enforce IDENTICAL transition rules. The split
         exists for future per-type customization. This case exercises
         the complaint_state_machine flow's OnUpdate trigger filtered
         by type=Complaint.
      3. Open status semantics: the case has been routed to a group's
         queue but not yet picked up by an agent. The Open -> In
         Progress transition is blocked until a case_manager assigns an
         agent who is a member of the assigned_group, satisfying the
         validate_inprogress_transition subflow's two-clause guard.
      4. THIS CASE IS THE CANONICAL GROUP-MEMBERSHIP-CLAUSE TEST for
         the case_agent's "Assigned only" ACL. The first clause
         (assigned_agent == current user) is FALSE because
         assigned_agent is empty. The second clause
         (current user is a member of assigned_group) is TRUE because
         the demo agent is a member of x_[scope]_demo_team. Therefore
         the demo agent can read this case ONLY via the group-
         membership clause - this is the inverse of cases 03, 04, 05,
         08, 09 where both clauses grant access.
      5. High priority is appropriate for an unassigned complaint at
         intake. Complaints typically warrant elevated urgency relative
         to General Inquiries (case 02 Open General Inquiry is Medium),
         and the High priority signals to the manager that this
         complaint should be triaged ahead of routine General Inquiries.
      6. NO assigned_agent, NO tasks, NO parties on this case. Open
         complaint cases have not yet been worked - parties are
         typically captured during the investigation phase
         (cases 03-05 and 08-09), not at intake.
      7. The choice value "Complaint" is exactly that string - capital
         C, lowercase rest. Not "complaint", not "COMPLAINT", not
         "Complaints".
      8. This case does NOT appear in the Agent Workspace's "My Open
         Cases" list because the list filter requires
         assigned_agent = current user, and this case has no
         assigned_agent. The demo agent reaches this case via the
         general case list backed by the group-membership ACL clause,
         not the personal "My Open Cases" widget.
      9. Without case 07 (and its Complaint siblings 08, 09, 10), the
         all_cases_by_type Manager View donut would have an empty
         Complaint slice - a one-type donut is not a meaningful
         visualization. This case's presence is REQUIRED for the
         Complaint slice to exist at all.
     10. The literal "[scope]" placeholder is preserved verbatim
         throughout the file - in the sys_class_name, sys_update_name,
         table attribute, inner element name, all cross-reference text
         values, and the file path. The PDI substitutes the auto-
         assigned concrete scope id at apply-time; pre-substituting
         here would break the substitution mechanism.
-->
<record_update table="x_[scope]_case">
    <x_[scope]_case action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <assigned_group display_value="x_[scope]_demo_team">x_[scope]_demo_team</assigned_group>
        <description>Synthetic Open complaint case awaiting agent assignment.</description>
        <priority>High</priority>
        <requester_email>requester-7@example.invalid</requester_email>
        <requester_name>Synthetic Requester Seven</requester_name>
        <status>Open</status>
        <subject>Demo case 07: Open (Complaint)</subject>
        <sys_class_name>x_[scope]_case</sys_class_name>
        <sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by>
        <sys_id>d2a92d7d0645409519a05256350fc65e</sys_id>
        <sys_package display_value="Case Management" source="x_[scope]">x_[scope]</sys_package>
        <sys_scope display_value="Case Management">x_[scope]</sys_scope>
        <sys_update_name>x_[scope]_case_demo_07</sys_update_name>
        <type>Complaint</type>
    </x_[scope]_case>
</record_update>
